Package: funfield
Type: Package
Title: Functional Field Models for Psychology
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Dustin", "Wood",
                  email = "dustinwood79@gmail.com",
                  role  = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tools for building, fitting, and visualizing functional
    field models in psychology. Models expected outcomes of actions in
    situations as covariance structures, estimates path coefficients
    from Elaborated Situational Judgment Test (ESJT) data via 'lavaan',
    and renders the results as field-style causal path diagrams.
    Includes helpers for data-quality screens, within-person deviation,
    moderator screening across trait batteries, and mediation /
    moderation decomposition. Most core functions assume the input data
    is structured with person, situation, and initiating-action columns
    ('p', 's', 'i') as the first three columns. See Wood (in preparation).
